<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                        Ambassador in China (
                        Stuart
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d217</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">217</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-06-04T16:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-06-04T16:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-04T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6–448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-04T17:00:00-04:00">June 4, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>842. Full text by urgent tel Ambs Jun 4 speech or statement<note n="90" xml:id="d217fn90">For text transmitted in telegram of June 5, by the
                        Ambassador in China, see Department of State, <hi rend="italic">United
                            States Relations With China</hi> (Washington, Government Printing
                        Office, 1949), p. 869.</note> would be appreciated since some news agencies
                    playing story as virtual US official demand to ChiGovt to suppress student
                    movement on pain no more aid. One version asserts Amb on instructions Dept
                    presented formal note ChiGovt demanding suppressions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
